<subSubSection pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1437,500,1319]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1076,1102]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Biology.</emphasis>
The only known ecological information about 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aldrich" authorityYear="1916" box="[837,951,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Sarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltata">
<emphasis box="[837,951,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">O. peltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is its relationship, presumably as a highly effective pollinator, with the mangrove 
<taxonomicName box="[596,864,1112,1138]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Laguncularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis box="[596,864,1112,1138]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Laguncularia racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) C.F. Gaertn. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.Brown" authorityYear="1810" box="[1073,1237,1112,1139]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Combretaceae</taxonomicName>
) (Sánchez-Núñez &amp; Mancera-Pineda 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
